CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1782544686
OL,3,CWhen will the record-breaking UK
OL,4,Cheatwave end?
OL,6,FParts of the south and south-east
OL,7,Fremain in the amber warning area into
OL,8,FSaturday as the heatwave remains in
OL,9,Fplace.
OL,11,FTogether with high humidity levels, it
OL,12,Fwill be a baking hot start to the
OL,13,Fweekend, and muggy and warm nights
OL,14,Fwill also be a feature of those
OL,15,Fconditions.
OL,17,FUrban areas will retain a lot of heat
OL,18,Fafter several days of high
OL,19,Ftemperatures.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1782544686
OL,3,CWhen will the record-breaking UK
OL,4,Cheatwave end?
OL,6,FBut by Saturday night, a frontal
OL,7,Fsystem, which is sweeping in from the
OL,8,Fwest, will mean the wind direction
OL,9,Fwill switch, and that will bring much
OL,10,Ffresher weather.
OL,12,FThis front will travel across the UK
OL,13,Ffrom the west to the east, and by
OL,14,FSunday morning, the heatwave in the
OL,15,Fsouth-east will eventually give way.
OL,17,FWhen will it feel cooler?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
